race.comment: STORM AWAY (3) flew home first-up in the Max Simmonds before a 3.6L defeat in the Belgravia Stakes at Listed level 18 days ago. He drops right back to Maiden company today however and the aid of an inside draw is a big tick. Rates highly on his performances this time in work and just needs to hold his form to shed the maiden tag. CONCHETTA'S DREAM (9) ran on strongly from the back half of the field on debut to be 0.7L off the winner over 1000m. She's been given some time to recover from that effort and now rises to 1200m with the tongue tie going on. Draws well and looks a big threat. FILA MIA (6) has disappointed her past couple, but her last run was in the Placid Ark Prelude. Back to a race like this should suit her much better and she can bounce back to form. DIAMOND WARRIOR (4) can improve now third-up and coming back to Maiden grade. JEMCONI (10) was solid on debut as favourite and looks suited by the slight rise in trip.
